<HL>
   International Brief -- Sanyo Electric Co.:
   Pretax Profit Gained 1.2%
   In the Fiscal First Half
</HL>
<DATE>
07/23/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A8
</SO>
<CO>
   SANYY
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Sanyo Electric Co. said consolidated pretax profit in the
first half ended May 31 rose 1.2% to 19.02 billion yen
($128.6 million) from 18.8 billion yen a year earlier.
   Net income edged up 2.8% to 5.71 billion yen, or 3.02 yen
a share, from 5.56 billion yen, or 2.95 yen a share.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Citing Japan's strong consumer spending, the company
reported sales of 676.17 billion yen, a 4.3% gain from 648.17
billion yen. Domestic sales rose 3% to 412.01 billion yen,
while overseas sales gained 6.4% to 264.15 billion yen.
   Sales of television sets and other visual products gained
14% to 122.35 billion yen.
   However, audio products sales declined 10% to 62.47
billion yen. Sales of household electric appliances rose 7.7%
to 163.15 billion yen.
   For the year ending in November, the company predicted
consolidated sales would rise to 1.45 trillion yen from 1.37
trillion yen a year ago. Pretax profit is seen at 47.5
billion yen, rising from 46.57 billion yen, with net income
standing at 17.5 billion yen, up from 16.84 billion yen.
</TEXT>
